Habitat. This species occurs in the humid Brazilian Amazonia, with specimens found in conservation areas around Manaus city. The specimens from the Estação Experimental de Silvicultura Florestal were collected by Malaise traps installed within scleromorphic scrub vegetation associated with white sand, known as campina ( sensu
Macedo & Prance 1978
), campinarana ( sensu Vel oso et al. 1991 ) or Amazon caatinga ( sensu
Anderson 1981
) (R. Ale-Rocha, pers. com. ). A female specimen from the Reserva Florestal Adolpho Ducke, however, was collected in dense ombrophilous forest ( sensu
Veloso et al. 1991
) (A. Somavilla, pers. com .).
